contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:48.219 --> 00:50.632
<i>Psychiatrists</i>
<i>have nothing on spies</i>

00:50.700 --> 00:54.283
<i>when it comes to over-analyzing</i>
<i>their friends' behavior.</i>

00:54.350 --> 00:55.926
<i>As a covert operative,</i>

00:55.994 --> 00:58.474
<i>you routinely trust</i>
<i>your co-workers with your life,</i>

00:58.541 --> 01:01.051
<i>so you tend to notice when</i>
<i>they start acting strangely.</i>

01:01.119 --> 01:03.732
(Michael) Jesse, you want to
tell us why we've come here?

01:03.799 --> 01:06.008
What? It's
a beautiful day, man.

01:06.076 --> 01:07.413
(Fiona)
Oh, please.

01:07.480 --> 01:09.690
First you complain
about how sandy the beach is,

01:09.757 --> 01:11.395
and then
you can't stop staring

01:11.462 --> 01:13.370
at the one woman
on South Beach

01:13.437 --> 01:14.744
who should <i>not</i> be
wearing a bikini.

01:14.812 --> 01:18.157
Who is the future
Mrs. Jesse Porter over there?

01:18.224 --> 01:21.436
[ Chuckles ]
She's not exactly my type.

01:21.503 --> 01:23.781
My old boss, Marv --
that's his wife.

01:23.848 --> 01:25.485
I heard
they were in town.

01:25.556 --> 01:26.992
And here we thought
it was just a coincidence

01:27.060 --> 01:28.397
you set up in front of
the Eden Roc Hotel.

01:28.464 --> 01:29.904
Well, you know
about the International

01:29.971 --> 01:31.711
Intelligence Conference
they're having here?

01:31.779 --> 01:34.486
Covert operatives and diplomats
from all over the world

01:34.554 --> 01:36.027
mingling in Miami.

01:36.095 --> 01:38.435
Michael has this weekend circled
on his calendar every year.

01:38.503 --> 01:40.544
All right, well, I should have
been straight with you guys.

01:40.614 --> 01:42.118
I just...Didn't think
you'd be comfortable

01:42.186 --> 01:43.389
bodysurfing
with a bunch of spies.

01:43.456 --> 01:44.796
So, what's your plan?

01:44.863 --> 01:46.803
Bump into your old boss,
build a sandcastle together,

01:46.871 --> 01:48.677
and he welcomes you back
with open arms?

01:48.745 --> 01:51.052
Marv knows about what
I was looking into before I got burned --

01:51.119 --> 01:52.725
the assassinations,
the arms dealing.

01:52.793 --> 01:54.496
He doesn't like it
any more than we do,

01:54.564 --> 01:56.973
so...
I was thinking, maybe...

01:57.041 --> 02:00.351
You <i>might</i> be able to lean
on him a little bit.

02:00.419 --> 02:02.158
Could help get our investigation
back on track.

02:02.226 --> 02:04.768
We do need <i>somebody</i> with
high-level federal connections.

02:04.836 --> 02:07.076
Sam's buddies
haven't turned up anything.

02:07.143 --> 02:09.583
Well, I take it
our beach day is over.

02:09.651 --> 02:13.430
Where do you suppose
old Marv is hiding?

02:14.737 --> 02:17.343
Well, if that was <i>my</i> wife,
I know where <i>I'd</i> be.

02:24.990 --> 02:26.725
Marv.

02:28.796 --> 02:30.063
I'm sorry.
Do we --

02:30.131 --> 02:31.733
Michael Westen.

02:31.800 --> 02:33.236
Yeah.
<i>That</i> Michael Westen.

02:33.304 --> 02:35.175
Probably don't want
to be seen with me.

02:35.243 --> 02:36.445
Not with him
either, huh?

02:39.588 --> 02:40.792
What do you want?

02:40.860 --> 02:42.696
Jesse hasn't stopped
working his last assignment.

02:42.766 --> 02:43.834
I've been helping him.

02:43.902 --> 02:45.137
There was
a failed bank heist

02:45.205 --> 02:47.043
a couple of months ago
here in Miami.

02:47.110 --> 02:50.184
We want to know which bank it was
and what they were trying to steal.

02:50.252 --> 02:51.354
I can't help you.
Sure you can.

02:51.422 --> 02:52.557
The bank
kept it out of the news,

02:52.625 --> 02:54.262
but they would have had
to report it.

02:54.330 --> 02:55.699
Call a friend at the Treasury.

02:55.768 --> 02:57.437
Hell, the FDIC might even know.

02:57.505 --> 02:59.509
No, I mean
I can't help you or Jesse.

02:59.577 --> 03:00.881
Not after what happened.

03:00.949 --> 03:03.951
Jesse is not guilty of what
he's accused of. Trust me.

03:04.018 --> 03:06.753
I never believed
what they said about Jesse.

03:06.821 --> 03:08.721
But I'm not about to do
any favors

03:08.789 --> 03:11.223
for a couple of burned spies.

03:11.291 --> 03:12.157
I'm sorry.

03:20.465 --> 03:21.766
He didn't go for it?

03:21.833 --> 03:23.968
We'll just
have to change Marv's mind,

03:24.035 --> 03:25.636
right, Michael?

03:32.375 --> 03:34.242
<i>International conferences</i>
<i>are good cover</i>

03:34.310 --> 03:36.211
<i>for run-of-the-mill</i>
<i>diplomatic spooks</i>

03:36.278 --> 03:37.945
<i>and black-bag operatives alike.</i>

03:38.013 --> 03:40.247
<i>One way to tell them apart --</i>
<i>their luggage.</i>

03:40.315 --> 03:42.849
<i>You don't bring</i>
<i>a high-speed-film camera</i>

03:42.917 --> 03:45.885
<i>to an event where nobody wants</i>
<i>their picture taken</i>

03:45.953 --> 03:49.588
<i>unless you want to bypass the</i>
<i>X-ray machines at the airport.</i>

03:49.656 --> 03:51.557
<i>Telephoto lenses</i>
<i>are a great place</i>

03:51.624 --> 03:54.025
<i>to store the illegal silencer</i>
<i>you're smuggling in.</i>

03:54.093 --> 03:55.393
What are we looking at?

03:55.460 --> 03:57.793
A Russian wet-work team,
if I had to guess.

03:57.861 --> 04:00.362
Spetsnaz. Definitely.
And they're here to work.

04:00.430 --> 04:01.996
What,
you think they're here

04:02.064 --> 04:03.698
to kill someone
on American soil?

04:03.765 --> 04:06.567
I don't think they're here for
the banquet food and seminars.

04:06.634 --> 04:08.067
They came heavy.

04:08.135 --> 04:09.602
What, you think
you're the target?

04:09.670 --> 04:12.739
Maybe, maybe not. Either way,
I'd love to know who is.

04:12.807 --> 04:14.542
Why don't we just
ask one of them?

04:19.482 --> 04:21.983
How about the pretty boy there?
Seems like the runt of the litter.

04:22.051 --> 04:24.453
Ooh. Almost
doesn't seem fair.

04:26.322 --> 04:28.190
[ Man speaking Russian ]

04:28.257 --> 04:29.757
[ Grunts ]
Oh! Hold the elevator!

04:29.825 --> 04:31.258
Oh!

04:31.326 --> 04:33.426
Bitch, what are you doing?
(Jesse) Language.

04:33.494 --> 04:35.392
Ladies first, man.
We'll get the next one.

04:37.061 --> 04:39.062
[ Elevator bell dings ]
See?

04:40.331 --> 04:42.398
It's okay, bud.

04:55.342 --> 04:56.975
[ Elevator bell dings ]

04:59.778 --> 05:02.345
<i>Nyet, nyet, nyet.</i>
Who's your target?

05:02.413 --> 05:05.247
[ Russian accent ]
No...English.

05:05.315 --> 05:07.382
Oh, we know better than that,
don't we, <i>bitch?</i>

05:07.450 --> 05:09.218
Got to go
and make this difficult.

05:11.889 --> 05:14.257
This was my idea.

05:14.325 --> 05:16.126
<i>I</i> should have
gotten to hit him.

05:18.796 --> 05:20.629
[ Jesse clears throat ]

05:20.697 --> 05:22.932
[ Muffled screaming ]

05:22.999 --> 05:24.200
Shhh!

05:24.267 --> 05:25.501
Even a day at the beach

05:25.569 --> 05:27.470
isn't a day at the beach
with you people.

05:28.950 --> 05:33.850
<font color=#00FFFF>Burn Notice 4x07</font>
<font color=#FFFF00>Past & Future Tense</font>
<font color=#FFFFFF>Original Air Date on July 22, 2010</font>

05:33.860 --> 05:37.860
-- Sync, corrected by <font color="#00ff00">elderman</font> --
-- for <font color=#00FFFF>www.addic7ed.com</font> --

05:37.922 --> 05:39.322
(Sam) Where is he?
Where you got him?

05:39.390 --> 05:40.857
(Fiona) You're
awfully fired up, Sam.

05:40.925 --> 05:42.291
Isn't this normally
your nap time?

05:42.359 --> 05:43.893
Yeah, but I love
interrogating Russians.

05:43.960 --> 05:45.494
They were my
all-time favorite bad --

05:45.562 --> 05:46.862
well, I'm the boss.
I called dibs.

05:46.930 --> 05:48.930
Wait a second. Mike,
that's not fair. Last time --

05:48.998 --> 05:51.366
Oh, you really think he's gonna side
with you over his girl?

05:51.434 --> 05:53.768
Guys! There's a wet-work team
on South Beach

05:53.836 --> 05:55.436
that might be here
to kill me.

05:55.504 --> 05:57.104
I would like
to find out <i>today.</i>

05:57.172 --> 05:58.872
Sam, you make
the introductions --

05:58.940 --> 06:00.941
I'm famous,
Fi's the hammer.

06:01.008 --> 06:03.609
Okay, so bad cop,
badder cop...Worse cop?

06:03.677 --> 06:05.110
I can live with that.

06:05.178 --> 06:07.446
<i>Under ideal circumstances,</i>

06:07.514 --> 06:09.881
<i>a good interrogation</i>
<i>unfolds slowly.</i>

06:09.949 --> 06:12.049
<i>But circumstances</i>
<i>are not always ideal.</i>

06:12.117 --> 06:13.851
<i>If you're operating on a clock,</i>

06:13.918 --> 06:16.519
<i>sometimes you have to get</i>
<i>right in your enemy's face</i>

06:16.587 --> 06:17.753
<i>and turn up the heat.</i>

06:17.821 --> 06:19.721
Now we're getting somewhere.
Alexi?

06:19.789 --> 06:21.188
Wow, that's
kind of a girly name

06:21.256 --> 06:22.556
for a Russian operative,
isn't it?

06:24.659 --> 06:26.893
Why are you in Miami?

06:28.228 --> 06:31.196
Come on, Alexi.
Who's your target?

06:31.263 --> 06:33.497
We know you guys
are here on business.

06:33.565 --> 06:36.400
Oh, look, a suppressor!
How'd that get in there?

06:36.468 --> 06:38.101
Oh, I get it.

06:38.169 --> 06:40.303
Yeah, I can
slap you around all day,

06:40.371 --> 06:42.772
and you're not gonna talk,
are you?

06:42.840 --> 06:44.240
You know Michael Westen?

06:47.310 --> 06:49.678
Is he your target?

06:49.745 --> 06:51.245
You joke.

06:51.313 --> 06:53.847
Everyone
in Russian special forces

06:53.915 --> 06:56.683
has heard the name "Westen."

06:56.751 --> 06:59.585
He's like the bogeyman,
not real.

06:59.653 --> 07:01.187
I don't know about that.

07:08.361 --> 07:09.694
That's fake.

07:09.762 --> 07:11.996
You can't be.

07:13.198 --> 07:15.032
[ Speaks Russian ]

07:47.961 --> 07:50.262
I won't talk.

07:50.329 --> 07:51.996
I can't.

07:52.064 --> 07:54.965
Okay, tough guy.
You can talk to our lady friend.

07:57.535 --> 07:59.636
Don't worry.
We're not gonna kill you.

07:59.704 --> 08:00.870
We don't have to.

08:00.938 --> 08:02.705
We can just
leave you here.

08:02.773 --> 08:04.974
And you can spend
the next three days

08:05.042 --> 08:06.809
getting very, very thirsty

08:06.877 --> 08:09.177
and wondering why
you didn't save your friends.

08:09.245 --> 08:11.346
What are you talking about?

08:11.414 --> 08:13.748
We can't
let your team strike.

08:13.815 --> 08:15.749
We don't have to
kill them either.

08:15.817 --> 08:17.484
All we have to do
is <i>stop</i> them.

08:17.552 --> 08:22.088
Tell us your mission,
and we'll spare their lives.

08:27.392 --> 08:28.625
It's been a while

08:28.693 --> 08:31.727
since I've heard
the sound of a Russian scream.

08:31.795 --> 08:32.995
I miss it.

08:35.864 --> 08:37.130
Have it your way.

08:38.566 --> 08:39.967
Paul Anderson.

08:40.034 --> 08:41.869
There's a good boy.

08:41.937 --> 08:42.904
[ Chuckles ]

08:42.971 --> 08:44.405
[ Switchblade clicks ]

08:44.473 --> 08:47.741
We're here for an old spy,
an American named Paul Anderson.

08:47.809 --> 08:50.910
He had a source in the Kremlin
during the cold war.

08:50.978 --> 08:53.579
We think maybe his source
is still in our government.

08:53.646 --> 08:55.747
So you're here
to interrogate him?

08:55.815 --> 08:58.183
Our leader, Vitali,
is a specialist.

08:58.250 --> 09:00.153
Where are you
gonna grab Anderson?

09:03.490 --> 09:06.491
He has job
at Bananafish Bar.

09:08.461 --> 09:10.161
That's all I know.

09:10.229 --> 09:12.197
Please.

09:12.264 --> 09:14.499
[ Muffled screaming ]

09:14.566 --> 09:16.500
It almost
doesn't seem fair.

09:16.568 --> 09:18.502
Alexi's a sweetheart,
really.

09:18.570 --> 09:20.103
At least
you're not the target.

09:20.171 --> 09:21.638
We got to warn Anderson.

09:21.706 --> 09:23.473
Do you know
where this bar is?

09:23.541 --> 09:26.575
Uh, yeah. It's a <i>bar.</i>
<i>I'll drive.</i>

09:26.643 --> 09:28.009
Fi, can you --

09:28.077 --> 09:29.211
babysit Alexi.

09:29.278 --> 09:31.146
I was gonna say,
"babysit <i>Jesse."</i>

09:31.214 --> 09:32.882
He wanted to stay close
to Marv.

09:32.949 --> 09:34.783
Just make sure
he doesn't get <i>too</i> close.

09:34.851 --> 09:36.551
It sounded to me
like Marv thought

09:36.619 --> 09:38.019
Jesse was actually innocent.

09:38.087 --> 09:39.720
And if he starts digging
and he finds out

09:39.788 --> 09:41.255
that I'm the one
who got Jesse fired,

09:41.323 --> 09:42.689
we could have
some real problems.

09:42.757 --> 09:44.424
So it's not enough
to burn the guy.

09:44.492 --> 09:46.226
Now we have to make sure
he <i>stays</i> burned?

09:46.293 --> 09:48.561
Fi, please.

09:48.629 --> 09:50.229
[ Sighs ]

10:02.841 --> 10:04.241
(Sam) Barkeep.
Yo.

10:04.309 --> 10:06.276
You know where we can find
a Paul Anderson?

10:06.343 --> 10:08.043
Yeah. Down there.
The end of the bar.

10:16.518 --> 10:18.085
Paul.

10:18.153 --> 10:19.987
No Paul here. I'm Chris.
What can I get you?

10:21.255 --> 10:22.455
Never mind.

10:22.523 --> 10:23.857
Damn it. The first guy.
I must have spooked him.

10:23.924 --> 10:25.258
He ran.

10:27.227 --> 10:29.495
Uh, no, Mike.
He didn't.

10:29.563 --> 10:30.930
[ Gun cocks ]

10:30.997 --> 10:33.899
Been a long time
since anybody called me "Paul."

10:33.966 --> 10:36.000
Take it easy.
I'm Mike. This is Sam.

10:36.068 --> 10:37.569
I don't want to upset you

10:37.636 --> 10:39.136
while you've got a gun
on my friend,

10:39.204 --> 10:40.571
but there's
a Russian black-ops team

10:40.639 --> 10:41.839
on its way
to kidnap and torture you.

10:44.075 --> 10:47.343
That's the worst news
I've heard all day.

10:47.411 --> 10:49.645
You guys
are nice enough fellas,

10:49.713 --> 10:53.182
but you dropped a name
that died about 20 years ago.

10:53.249 --> 10:55.317
Look, we're friendlies.

10:55.385 --> 10:58.587
I used to be on the teams.
Mike worked for the company.

10:58.655 --> 11:01.523
I've got a Spetsnaz officer
curled up in a steamer trunk.

11:01.591 --> 11:03.558
He told me four of his buddies

11:03.626 --> 11:05.093
are on their way here now
to kidnap you.

11:06.395 --> 11:08.462
That's funny.
It's really not.

11:08.530 --> 11:10.530
Well, I hope someday
you think it is.

11:10.598 --> 11:12.966
So, how does a retired spy
land back on the radar?

11:14.502 --> 11:18.305
All right, back in '86,
the Russians had these birds

11:18.373 --> 11:22.642
that could fly into our com
satellites and knock them out.

11:22.710 --> 11:23.910
I had a source in the Kremlin --

11:23.977 --> 11:25.845
wait a second --
you're the guy who got the specs

11:25.912 --> 11:27.413
on the Russian
hunter/killer satellites?

11:27.480 --> 11:28.447
That was <i>you?</i>

11:28.515 --> 11:30.482
I had to play it
off-the-books

11:30.550 --> 11:33.852
because of this numnuts
Congressman named Bill Cowley.

11:33.920 --> 11:36.388
You mean the Chairman
of the House Intelligence

11:36.455 --> 11:38.289
Oversight Committee
Bill Cowley?

11:38.357 --> 11:40.225
Mike, you know,
he's the keynote speaker

11:40.292 --> 11:41.826
at the convention
this weekend.

11:41.894 --> 11:43.528
Well, I got sloppy
the other night.

11:43.596 --> 11:45.563
I drank way too much.

11:45.631 --> 11:48.233
I got on
the Internet message board,

11:48.300 --> 11:49.834
and I ripped him a good one.

11:49.902 --> 11:51.402
You outed yourself.

11:51.470 --> 11:53.004
I said I was sloppy.
Uh, guys, they're here.

11:57.743 --> 11:59.544
We keep this quiet,
stay low,

11:59.611 --> 12:01.045
this doesn't have to
become a scene.

12:01.112 --> 12:03.046
What are you
talking about "we"?

12:03.114 --> 12:04.881
It's my mess.
I'll clean it up.

12:04.949 --> 12:06.083
Sorry, old timer.

12:06.150 --> 12:07.484
Can't be picking off bad guys

12:07.552 --> 12:08.952
in the middle
of a crowded bar.

12:09.020 --> 12:10.820
You're just gonna have to
accept our help.

12:10.888 --> 12:12.689
All right.

12:12.756 --> 12:14.857
But if you call me
"old timer" again,

12:14.925 --> 12:17.593
you're gonna be wearing
your ass around your head.

12:18.762 --> 12:19.461
Like a hat.

12:23.800 --> 12:25.366
[ Crowd cheering ]

12:26.835 --> 12:29.069
Three guesses
which one's Vitali.

12:32.170 --> 12:33.903
Looks like
the typical Russian tactics --

12:33.970 --> 12:35.603
they block off the exits
and advance

12:35.671 --> 12:37.871
about as fast as a glacier
until they find the target.

12:37.938 --> 12:39.538
I guess we'll
have to move quickly.

12:39.606 --> 12:41.406
Keep your eye on Paul.
I'll make a path.

12:41.474 --> 12:43.141
<i>When you're being hunted</i>
<i>in a crowd,</i>

12:43.209 --> 12:45.076
<i>your biggest advantage is,</i>

12:45.144 --> 12:48.779
<i>your opponents can't maintain</i>
<i>visual contact with each other.</i>

12:48.847 --> 12:52.015
<i>The key is to move without</i>
<i>drawing attention to yourself.</i>

12:52.083 --> 12:55.018
<i>When you can, you disguise</i>
<i>your actions as something else.</i>

12:55.085 --> 12:56.786
Serge's had
way too much to drink!

12:58.989 --> 13:01.724
<i>When you can't,</i>
<i>you strike fast and hard.</i>

13:07.697 --> 13:08.864
Boris.

13:08.931 --> 13:10.565
[ Grunts ]

13:11.967 --> 13:14.435
They always
answer to "Boris."

13:14.502 --> 13:18.271
You were right.
It is more fun without the guns.

13:18.339 --> 13:20.239
<i>Then you calmly</i>
<i>move for the exits</i>

13:20.307 --> 13:21.807
<i>and get the hell out of there.</i>

13:25.032 --> 13:26.999
I appreciate
the thought, fellas,

13:27.067 --> 13:29.668
but if this dump
is your idea of a safe house,

13:29.736 --> 13:30.802
thanks, but --

13:30.870 --> 13:32.604
this is not a --
I <i>live</i> here.

13:32.672 --> 13:34.205
Look, just
stay the night, okay?

13:34.273 --> 13:36.374
Vitali and his boys
are not gonna come knockin'.

13:36.442 --> 13:37.575
We'll make some calls,

13:37.642 --> 13:39.176
try and get you
federal protection.

13:39.244 --> 13:40.177
That's not an option.

13:40.245 --> 13:41.411
When I retired,

13:41.479 --> 13:42.913
they didn't exactly give me
a gold watch.

13:42.980 --> 13:44.047
You were burned?

13:44.115 --> 13:45.681
No, but I'm...
A little toasty.

13:45.749 --> 13:47.716
You got to have <i>some</i> friends
on the inside.

13:47.784 --> 13:49.184
Most of my friends are dead,

13:49.252 --> 13:51.220
and the rest of them
are pissed off at me.

13:51.287 --> 13:52.954
That sounds familiar.
[ sighs ]

13:53.022 --> 13:54.789
I tell you what --
you've done enough.

13:54.857 --> 13:56.124
I should just get going.

13:56.191 --> 13:57.591
(Fiona) Well,
who do we have here?

13:59.427 --> 14:02.696
Well, I -- I guess
I could stay the night.

14:02.763 --> 14:05.531
It was like watching
a younger version of myself

14:05.599 --> 14:08.001
cutting through
those Russians, you know?

14:08.069 --> 14:10.770
They used to call it
"karate,"

14:10.838 --> 14:12.705
but I think they got
a new word for it now.

14:12.773 --> 14:13.940
Foreplay.

14:14.008 --> 14:15.141
Hello.

14:16.543 --> 14:18.813
Where'd you find
this beautiful creature?

14:18.880 --> 14:20.214
Let's focus.

14:20.282 --> 14:21.582
Now that the Russians know

14:21.649 --> 14:23.150
you're out in the cold,
it's open season.

14:23.217 --> 14:24.985
If they're willing to send
one Vitali stateside,

14:25.052 --> 14:27.453
they'll keep sending Vitalis
until you're answering questions

14:27.521 --> 14:28.954
with electrodes
all over your face.

14:29.022 --> 14:31.323
I still won't talk.
That's option "B."

14:31.391 --> 14:32.891
Option "A" is,
we get you back in.

14:32.959 --> 14:35.093
(Sam) You need a new identity,
a pension transfer,

14:35.161 --> 14:36.894
and your name
back on the do-not-touch list.

14:36.962 --> 14:38.996
Now, l-look, you said
you had some dirt on Cowley.

14:39.064 --> 14:40.130
Now's the time to use it.

14:40.198 --> 14:42.433
One of my guys
at the bureau told me

14:42.500 --> 14:44.168
Cowley has a nice place
out on Key Biscayne.

14:44.236 --> 14:46.536
Tomorrow morning, I'll try and
separate him from his entourage,

14:46.604 --> 14:47.770
and I'll
meet you guys there.

14:47.838 --> 14:49.171
Well, the file's at my place,

14:49.239 --> 14:51.806
and I probably got
four new Russian neighbors

14:51.874 --> 14:53.174
staking it out.

14:53.241 --> 14:55.275
Think we should try and grab it
while it's still dark?

14:55.343 --> 14:56.776
No, let's do it tomorrow.

14:56.844 --> 14:58.311
I want them
to see me coming.

14:58.378 --> 15:00.012
Get some sleep, Paul.

15:03.315 --> 15:05.115
I need to talk to you
about Jesse.

15:05.182 --> 15:07.217
Have you two gotten
in front of Marv yet?

15:07.284 --> 15:09.286
I'm gonna bump into him
in the morning.

15:09.354 --> 15:10.623
I want to talk about --

15:10.690 --> 15:12.125
not now.
Not in front of...

15:12.193 --> 15:14.428
Just do this for me,
please?

15:16.764 --> 15:18.631
[ Sighs ]

15:18.699 --> 15:21.100
Well, Mike,
<i>I</i> still love ya.

15:21.168 --> 15:23.769
Have fun with
the ghost of Christmas future.

15:36.480 --> 15:38.080
Oh, my God!

15:38.148 --> 15:39.115
Marv?!

15:40.717 --> 15:43.085
It's Barbara!

15:43.153 --> 15:44.853
We met in Toronto.

15:44.921 --> 15:47.622
I <i>have</i> lost a few pounds.
Maybe you don't recognize me.

15:47.689 --> 15:49.357
In Toronto?
At the conference?

15:49.424 --> 15:51.292
You gave that great talk

15:51.360 --> 15:53.894
on data mining
in the near East -- genius.

15:53.962 --> 15:55.695
I came up afterwards
and said so.

15:55.763 --> 15:58.030
Oh, yeah.
That's great. That's great.

15:58.098 --> 16:00.099
We should get a drink.

16:00.167 --> 16:01.100
I-I-I...

16:01.168 --> 16:02.667
You know, I'm here

16:02.735 --> 16:05.269
representing this amazing
new translation software.

16:05.337 --> 16:07.504
500 dialects,
incredible semantic nuance.

16:07.572 --> 16:09.406
Oh, you m-- you mean
like a business thing.

16:10.475 --> 16:13.543
Um...Um, I --

16:13.611 --> 16:16.746
o-or we could meet...
Privately.

16:16.813 --> 16:18.547
Room 337.

16:18.615 --> 16:20.249
Show you my brochure.

16:23.319 --> 16:25.386
Great.
Yes, that would be great.

16:25.454 --> 16:26.854
Of course -- Barbara!

16:26.922 --> 16:30.758
Yes, I remember!
I -- oh, it's wonderful!

16:30.825 --> 16:32.226
[ Sighs softly ]

16:35.362 --> 16:36.296
We in?

16:36.363 --> 16:37.830
No Marv can resist me.

16:37.898 --> 16:39.298
All right, I owe you.

16:39.366 --> 16:40.466
I might <i>really</i> owe you.

16:40.533 --> 16:41.934
Marv's in a good position

16:42.002 --> 16:43.669
to find out more
about why I got fired.

16:43.736 --> 16:45.737
You sound like Michael
after he got burned.

16:45.804 --> 16:48.339
The only thing <i>he</i> managed to do
was waste a year of his life.

16:48.407 --> 16:51.241
Different circumstances,
Fi.

16:53.878 --> 16:55.778
Jesse, wait.

16:55.846 --> 16:58.147
Take it from someone who's
had to watch this show before.

16:58.215 --> 17:01.950
You want to solve this big
mystery that spans the globe,

17:02.018 --> 17:03.051
you go ahead.

17:03.119 --> 17:04.653
But after that...

17:04.720 --> 17:08.888
Try to do something good
in your own corner of it.

17:08.957 --> 17:11.758
Your past is your past.
It's not coming back.

17:11.825 --> 17:14.660
Fi, that all sounds, uh...
Really healthy.

17:14.728 --> 17:16.595
I can't just walk away.

17:16.663 --> 17:18.431
I'm not stopping till the people

17:18.499 --> 17:20.567
that got me burned are six feet under.

17:20.635 --> 17:21.768
That's just what it is.

17:25.939 --> 17:28.607
<i>Spies and politicians tend</i>
<i>not to get along very well.</i>

17:28.675 --> 17:30.109
<i>Politicians see spies</i>

17:30.176 --> 17:32.444
<i>as vitally important</i>
<i>in the national interest,</i>

17:32.512 --> 17:34.980
<i>right up to the point where</i>
<i>they deny ever meeting them</i>

17:35.047 --> 17:36.414
<i>and abandon them entirely.</i>

17:36.482 --> 17:38.416
<i>It makes for</i>
<i>a tough working relationship.</i>

17:38.483 --> 17:40.317
Sir!
Congressman!

17:40.385 --> 17:42.819
Sir. Congressman Cowley.
Could I talk to you for a minute, please?

17:42.887 --> 17:44.154
I'm sorry.

17:44.222 --> 17:45.956
We're late for a press event
at the Grove Boardwalk.

17:46.023 --> 17:47.991
No, look -- I need to talk to
your boss right now in private.

17:48.058 --> 17:49.358
This is a very
sensitive matter for me.

17:49.426 --> 17:51.694
I don't care if it's
a national-security matter.

17:51.762 --> 17:53.561
No one gets
in front of the Congressman

17:53.629 --> 17:54.829
without an appointment.

17:54.897 --> 17:56.430
Thanks for your support.

17:56.498 --> 17:59.567
Sir, I'm a war vet, okay?
This is about my disability.

17:59.635 --> 18:01.602
You know, I'm
one of your constituents.

18:01.670 --> 18:02.903
Yeah, but just one.

18:05.306 --> 18:06.973
Sir, please, come on.

18:07.041 --> 18:09.442
I mean, who pays
for your fancy car?

18:09.510 --> 18:11.311
Joe taxpayer, that's who.

18:11.378 --> 18:12.478
This isn't over.

18:12.546 --> 18:15.581
[ Cellphone rings ]

18:15.649 --> 18:17.049
[ Sighs ]

18:17.117 --> 18:19.851
Sam, would you still love me
if I switched to autumn colors?

18:19.919 --> 18:21.185
Uh, yes, but not as much.

18:21.253 --> 18:22.887
Look, Maddy,
we need your help.

18:22.955 --> 18:25.523
I got to corral a Congressman
and deliver him to Mike.

18:25.591 --> 18:27.558
Are you up for it?
Maybe. Who is it?

18:27.626 --> 18:28.959
You know Bill Cowley?

18:29.027 --> 18:31.261
Is he that guy with that
obnoxious "good ol' boy" shtick?

18:31.329 --> 18:32.662
I always want to slap him.

18:32.730 --> 18:35.231
Yeah. You meet me
at the Grove Boardwalk,

18:35.299 --> 18:36.832
you may just get the chance.

18:41.571 --> 18:43.238
(Paul) That's me --
the corner apartment.

18:43.306 --> 18:45.240
(Michael) Could you have
picked an easier place

18:45.308 --> 18:46.674
for hostiles to stake out?

18:48.510 --> 18:51.212
Yeah, like an apartment
over a night club.

18:51.279 --> 18:53.780
Vitali's got a nice,
tight net set up.

18:53.848 --> 18:55.748
Smart deployment,
great field of vision.

18:55.816 --> 18:57.583
He's a pro.

18:57.651 --> 18:59.285
What?

18:59.352 --> 19:01.119
You know something?
You remind me of <i>me.</i>

19:02.622 --> 19:04.622
What, do you wake up
three or four times

19:04.690 --> 19:06.156
in the middle of the night?

19:06.224 --> 19:08.824
I could tell you it gets better,
but I'd be lying.

19:08.892 --> 19:11.026
After a while, you just
start collecting ghosts.

19:13.263 --> 19:15.163
You don't seem all that haunted.

19:15.231 --> 19:17.031
Well, rum helps...
A lot.

19:19.468 --> 19:22.036
There's no good angle
for approach.

19:22.103 --> 19:23.070
There will be.

19:24.906 --> 19:26.940
Best case, they leave town.

19:27.007 --> 19:28.975
Worst case, you get the file
and head out back.

19:29.043 --> 19:30.576
I'll meet you there
in five minutes.

19:30.644 --> 19:33.212
They'll still be busy dealing
with Alexi's new wardrobe.

19:39.185 --> 19:41.419
Let's go.
Everybody out.

19:41.487 --> 19:43.087
Everyone's invited.

19:43.155 --> 19:45.022
You on the bench.

19:45.090 --> 19:48.625
That's right. Keep your hands
where I can see them.

19:51.829 --> 19:55.064
Who are you?
What is this?

19:55.132 --> 19:55.998
I'm Michael Westen.

19:57.767 --> 19:58.600
Yeah.
That one.

19:59.803 --> 20:01.470
Mr. Westen.

20:03.339 --> 20:05.606
We have no problem with you.

20:05.674 --> 20:07.741
You are wrong, Vitali.
We have a <i>big</i> problem.

20:07.809 --> 20:09.710
You're hunting an American spy
in my town.

20:09.777 --> 20:11.011
I'm offended.

20:11.078 --> 20:12.779
Paul Anderson is a snake.

20:12.846 --> 20:15.547
Then I'm a snake, too.

20:15.615 --> 20:18.650
Now, if I were to take the tape
off your man Alexi's mouth,

20:18.718 --> 20:19.884
he's probably gonna beg

20:19.952 --> 20:21.486
for permission
to pack up and go home.

20:21.553 --> 20:24.455
I suggest you join him.

20:24.522 --> 20:27.624
Such a decision is not up to me.

20:27.691 --> 20:30.026
We have our orders.

20:30.094 --> 20:32.928
I'm afraid we are,
you would say, at a crossroad.

20:32.996 --> 20:35.363
<i>I'd</i> say you have an hour
to get out of Miami,

20:35.431 --> 20:37.598
or there's not going to be
as many of you.

20:37.666 --> 20:39.233
I'm sorry, Alexi.

20:39.301 --> 20:41.935
But the mission comes first.

20:42.003 --> 20:45.538
Your man is packed with enough
C-4 to take out all of us.

20:45.606 --> 20:46.773
Put the gun down.

20:46.841 --> 20:50.542
I kill Michael Westen,
I am Russian hero.

20:52.745 --> 20:55.280
This is a radio transmitter
with a dead-man switch.

20:55.348 --> 20:56.882
Well, in this case,
dead <i>men.</i>

20:58.050 --> 21:00.651
You shoot me, I drop this.

21:00.719 --> 21:03.487
No more Alexi, no more Vitali,

21:03.554 --> 21:04.621
no more...

21:04.689 --> 21:05.555
That guy.

21:08.625 --> 21:11.293
Now, put your weapons
down now!

21:11.361 --> 21:12.494
Now!

21:20.335 --> 21:23.370
After Paul, you are next.

21:23.438 --> 21:24.904
Delightful.

21:26.207 --> 21:28.941
Now, you shoot at me
before I'm out of range,

21:29.009 --> 21:31.043
you'll be sharing
each other's caskets.

21:42.754 --> 21:44.321
Old timer, come on.

21:44.389 --> 21:46.089
Let's go!
We're clear!

21:48.158 --> 21:49.258
Damn it.

21:55.565 --> 21:56.598
Well?

21:56.666 --> 21:57.799
Well,
I can't remember.

21:57.867 --> 21:59.267
I can't remember
the combination.

21:59.334 --> 22:01.034
I must have had too many
last night.

22:01.102 --> 22:02.670
I'm a little foggy.

22:02.737 --> 22:04.638
Jesus, we got 5 minutes,
maybe 10,

22:04.706 --> 22:06.607
while they deal
with this guy's vest.

22:06.675 --> 22:07.641
Can you crack it?

22:07.709 --> 22:10.643
I was trained
to do this by touch.

22:10.711 --> 22:14.513
I feel the click of the pins

22:14.581 --> 22:16.915
in my fingerprints.

22:16.983 --> 22:18.850
Well, I was trained
to <i>listen.</i>

22:18.918 --> 22:19.951
Well, then, listen!

22:22.621 --> 22:24.389
[ Sighs ]

22:25.724 --> 22:26.591
Well?

22:31.262 --> 22:33.964
Well?
We got to kill the outside noise
and the vibrations.

22:34.032 --> 22:35.533
Help me move the safe.

22:35.600 --> 22:38.402
<i>If you need a microphone</i>
<i>but you only have a speaker,</i>

22:38.470 --> 22:39.936
<i>you don't have a problem.</i>

22:40.004 --> 22:41.638
<i>Both have magnets and coils</i>

22:41.705 --> 22:44.238
<i>that conduct sound</i>
<i>in roughly the same way.</i>

22:44.306 --> 22:46.137
<i>So you can just</i>
<i>plug a pair of headphones</i>

22:46.205 --> 22:48.905
<i>into a stereo's auxiliary jack</i>
<i>and crank the volume.</i>

22:48.973 --> 22:51.107
<i>It's not quite good enough</i>
<i>for karaoke,</i>

22:51.175 --> 22:53.709
<i>but you'll be able to hear</i>
<i>even faint noises</i>

22:53.777 --> 22:56.544
<i>like the discs</i>
<i>in a safe's locking mechanism</i>

22:56.612 --> 22:58.446
<i>clicking into position.</i>

22:58.513 --> 22:59.246
Eight...

23:01.615 --> 23:03.916
[ Dial clicking ]

23:03.984 --> 23:05.351
[ Lock clicks ]

23:05.419 --> 23:06.618
20.
Shhh!

23:07.854 --> 23:08.987
[ Dial clicking ]

23:09.055 --> 23:10.255
[ Lock clicks ]

23:13.725 --> 23:17.661
I can't believe I couldn't
remember the day my mother died.

23:17.729 --> 23:19.829
(Man) [ in distance ]
Boss, over here!

23:19.897 --> 23:21.531
Okay, they're here.

23:21.598 --> 23:23.665
Finally I get to kill
some Russians.

23:23.733 --> 23:26.168
Not now!
Let's go.

23:26.235 --> 23:28.303
Anyone ever tell you
you're no fun?

23:28.371 --> 23:29.938
All the time.
Get down!

23:34.242 --> 23:36.543
Whoa! This is fun.
[ laughs ]

23:36.611 --> 23:37.844
Get in the car!

23:37.912 --> 23:39.512
[ Engine turns over ]

23:39.580 --> 23:41.647
[ Gunshots, tires screech ]

23:54.072 --> 23:55.572
[ Tires screeching ]

23:57.504 --> 23:58.672
I hope you're having fun.

23:58.739 --> 24:01.506
We lost them
about three miles back.

24:01.574 --> 24:03.108
I'm just being careful.

24:03.176 --> 24:04.976
Now, let's see what I got here.

24:05.044 --> 24:08.312
You get a little older, you want
to double-check everything.

24:08.380 --> 24:10.046
Here we go.

24:10.114 --> 24:13.449
You sure that's enough
to put Cowley in a corner?

24:13.516 --> 24:15.084
This is his signature

24:15.151 --> 24:17.220
under a letter to a Marine General

24:17.287 --> 24:19.922
urging an illegal deployment
into BogotÃ¡, 1988.

24:19.990 --> 24:22.792
14 of our boys K.I.A.

24:22.859 --> 24:24.192
We weren't
<i>in</i> BogotÃ¡ in '88.

24:24.260 --> 24:26.194
Cowley covered it up.

24:26.262 --> 24:28.096
[ Engine revving ]

24:28.164 --> 24:30.364
Jesus. Where the hell
did they come from?

24:30.432 --> 24:31.532
All right!

24:31.600 --> 24:32.967
[ Tires screech ]

24:35.136 --> 24:36.403
Well, how'd they find us?

24:36.470 --> 24:37.637
Oh, they got to have
satellite support.

24:37.705 --> 24:38.838
Have what?

24:38.905 --> 24:40.873
Technology has improved a bit

24:40.940 --> 24:43.175
since the last time
you stole their specs.

24:51.849 --> 24:54.350
Stop doing that!
Stop that right now!

24:54.418 --> 24:55.284
What?

24:55.352 --> 24:57.686
[ Tires screech ]

25:08.762 --> 25:11.062
[ Horns honking ]

25:11.129 --> 25:12.529
Got to be kidding me!

25:12.597 --> 25:15.665
(Paul) The Russians are trying
to decide whether to snatch me

25:15.732 --> 25:18.099
right here in the middle
of Bayshore Drive.

25:18.167 --> 25:19.600
Vitali won't
make a move here.

25:19.668 --> 25:21.702
As long as he knows
he's got eyes in the sky,

25:21.770 --> 25:23.005
he knows we can't lose them.

25:23.072 --> 25:24.273
What a mess.

25:24.341 --> 25:26.476
But you got to admit,
it's kind of funny.

25:26.544 --> 25:28.678
No. No, I don't
got to admit that. No.

25:28.746 --> 25:30.079
I'll be right back.

25:34.451 --> 25:37.553
<i>As dangerous</i>
<i>as a high-speed chase can be,</i>

25:37.620 --> 25:39.554
<i>there's nothing</i>
<i>quite as treacherous</i>

25:39.622 --> 25:40.889
<i>as a</i> no-speed <i>chase.</i>

25:40.957 --> 25:43.224
<i>If you get pursued</i>
<i>into bad traffic,</i>

25:43.292 --> 25:45.827
<i>your operating paradigm</i>
<i>has to shift.</i>

25:45.895 --> 25:48.696
<i>Your car's no longer</i>
<i>being pursued --</i> you <i>are.</i>

25:48.764 --> 25:50.564
<i>Just because</i>
<i>your car can't move</i>

25:50.632 --> 25:52.532
<i>doesn't mean you can't.</i>

25:57.504 --> 25:59.405
Oh, you shouldn't have.

26:02.408 --> 26:04.175
[ Speaking Russian ]

26:04.243 --> 26:06.277
[ Tires screech ]

26:18.054 --> 26:20.221
So, that woman
you're with -- your fiancÃ©e?

26:20.289 --> 26:22.390
Not my fiancÃ©e.
Fiona.

26:22.457 --> 26:24.324
Wound a little tight,
aren't you?

26:24.392 --> 26:26.859
Paul, now would be a good time
to light that on fire

26:26.927 --> 26:29.028
and give them
something else to look at.

26:29.096 --> 26:30.796
Make it count.
I only got one of those.

26:41.305 --> 26:43.106
[ Man yelling in Russian ]

26:43.173 --> 26:44.507
Ho, ho!

26:48.812 --> 26:50.045
[ Cellphone rings ]

26:50.113 --> 26:52.280
(Cowley) Sure, I'd love to take
a few questions.

26:52.348 --> 26:55.517
Mike, please tell me you're not calling
from a Siberian Gulag.

26:55.584 --> 26:57.351
Not yet. We got the file.
Are you ready for us?

26:57.419 --> 26:58.652
Uh, about to be.

26:58.720 --> 27:00.721
Your mom is collecting
the Congressman as we speak.

27:00.788 --> 27:02.789
My mother?!
Well, there wasn't really enough time to explain.

27:02.856 --> 27:03.923
No, there isn't.

27:03.991 --> 27:05.491
The Russians have satellite support.

27:05.559 --> 27:07.459
We can drive all we want,
but sooner or later,

27:07.527 --> 27:09.728
we're gonna be staring down
the barrel of Vitali's A.K.

27:09.796 --> 27:11.830
Don't you worry, Mikey.
Your mom is clutch.

27:11.898 --> 27:15.700
Together we can make this
a safer, more prosperous Miami.

27:15.767 --> 27:17.668
Thank you.
Thank you all very much.

27:17.736 --> 27:19.670
Hey, how are you?
Good to see you again.

27:19.738 --> 27:22.472
Good to see you.
Thank you. Thank you, sir.

27:22.540 --> 27:23.573
Bill?

27:23.641 --> 27:24.741
Bill!

27:24.808 --> 27:29.112
It's Helen!
From Yale. Helen Foxvog.

27:29.179 --> 27:31.046
"Foxy"?

27:31.114 --> 27:32.114
Hey. Hello.

27:32.182 --> 27:33.615
Helen.
[ chuckles ]

27:33.683 --> 27:35.284
Listen, um...

27:35.351 --> 27:37.386
Tell your people
that you, uh, don't feel well

27:37.453 --> 27:39.054
and you want
to drive home alone,

27:39.121 --> 27:40.655
because you and I
have a meeting

27:40.723 --> 27:42.357
with Paul Anderson
at your house.

27:42.425 --> 27:44.960
And he's ready to talk all about
the Colombian thing if you don't.

27:45.028 --> 27:46.194
[ Laughs ]

27:48.231 --> 27:51.466
Tell him...

27:51.534 --> 27:53.467
I'll meet him at my office
tomorrow.

27:53.535 --> 27:55.767
Oh, actually, no.
It's <i>now!</i> [ chuckles ]

27:55.835 --> 27:57.166
Or I'm gonna start screaming

27:57.234 --> 27:58.734
about our love affair
in the '70s

27:58.802 --> 28:00.969
and your
secret grandchildren.

28:01.037 --> 28:02.971
Caroline
and little Jack --

28:03.039 --> 28:04.739
they're dying to meet you.

28:06.776 --> 28:09.077
I don't feel well.
I'm gonna...Take the car home.

28:16.916 --> 28:18.683
I'm here.

28:18.751 --> 28:20.884
Almost.
Come on in.

28:22.287 --> 28:24.154
Listen,
I got to be honest --

28:24.221 --> 28:27.356
we're very satisfied
with our translation software.

28:27.424 --> 28:28.958
Yeah,
about that...

28:29.025 --> 28:30.493
Hey, Marv.

28:32.929 --> 28:35.464
Look, I gave your department
eight years of my life,

28:35.565 --> 28:37.466
and I got kicked out
over some garbage.

28:37.534 --> 28:39.068
The least you can do
is hear me out.

28:39.135 --> 28:40.335
Or we could call your wife.

28:40.403 --> 28:42.170
Come on.
You know me, man.

28:42.238 --> 28:43.905
You know I didn't do
what they said I did.

28:43.973 --> 28:45.340
No.
I <i>don't</i> know that.

28:45.407 --> 28:47.142
I'd like to believe it, yes.

28:47.209 --> 28:48.843
What I <i>do</i> know
is that an effort was made

28:48.911 --> 28:50.311
to hack
into an eyes-only file --

28:50.379 --> 28:52.746
an effort that was traced back
to your login, your password.

28:52.814 --> 28:54.581
Marv, you can't believe
that I would have --

28:54.649 --> 28:56.917
it doesn't matter
what <i>I</i> believe! No! No! No!

28:56.985 --> 28:59.019
There's too much evidence
against you, Jess.

28:59.087 --> 29:00.855
I got too close.
That's what happened.

29:00.922 --> 29:02.723
Marv, someone's out there
starting wars.

29:02.791 --> 29:04.491
They're knocking off
labor leaders,

29:04.559 --> 29:07.027
burning food supplies, and
they're getting rich doing it.

29:07.094 --> 29:08.762
I was <i>this</i> close,
so they had me burned.

29:08.829 --> 29:10.730
Look, even
if that were true --

29:10.798 --> 29:12.197
I'm still working
this thing.

29:12.265 --> 29:14.332
Maybe it clears my name.
Maybe it doesn't.

29:14.400 --> 29:16.167
But somebody's
got to do it.

29:16.235 --> 29:18.535
All I need from you
is the name of a bank.

29:18.603 --> 29:20.237
But you really can't give me
that much?

29:22.440 --> 29:23.773
What bank?

29:23.841 --> 29:25.941
Best lead I got says
the folks we're looking for

29:26.009 --> 29:28.510
tried to hit a safety-deposit
box on the 4th of last month.

29:28.578 --> 29:30.779
Bank kept it quiet.
No cops, no news coverage.

29:30.846 --> 29:33.380
But they must have reported it
to insurance, right?

29:33.448 --> 29:35.515
All right,
I'll make a couple of calls,

29:35.583 --> 29:37.216
but I can't
see you again, Jess.

29:37.284 --> 29:38.151
Ever.

29:41.087 --> 29:43.621
Tomorrow night,
I'll meet this...

29:43.688 --> 29:45.689
<i>Person</i>
<i>at the hotel bar.</i>

29:45.756 --> 29:47.691
After Elise goes to sleep.

29:47.758 --> 29:48.792
It's a date.

29:55.899 --> 29:57.767
(Sam) They're waiting
for you, sir.

29:57.835 --> 29:58.868
(Cowley) "They"?

29:58.936 --> 30:01.002
Who does Paul have
with him?

30:01.070 --> 30:02.935
It's a surprise.

30:16.141 --> 30:18.742
Anderson, have you
lost your goddamn mind?

30:18.810 --> 30:20.077
Hello, bill.

30:20.145 --> 30:22.579
Michael Westen.
I don't know if you two met.

30:22.647 --> 30:24.014
I'm well aware of who he is.

30:24.081 --> 30:26.182
Congressman,
we don't have a lot of time.

30:26.250 --> 30:29.084
There's a Russian black-ops team
on its way to kidnap Paul.

30:29.152 --> 30:30.419
[ Chuckling ] Right.

30:30.486 --> 30:31.953
I'm sure this washout's

30:32.021 --> 30:34.188
right at the top
of their to-do list.

30:34.256 --> 30:36.257
Listen, you smug bastard.

30:36.324 --> 30:39.226
The cold war
wasn't so cold for me.

30:39.293 --> 30:41.861
I didn't like the people.
They didn't like me.

30:41.929 --> 30:44.663
I think what Paul is trying to say
is that he needs protection.

30:44.731 --> 30:47.165
And you can make that happen
just by picking up the phone.

30:47.233 --> 30:48.733
Or not.

30:48.801 --> 30:50.601
Maybe I'd just rather
take my chances

30:50.669 --> 30:51.602
and see what happens.

30:56.741 --> 30:58.675
This was <i>your</i> idea,
wasn't it?

30:58.742 --> 31:01.344
Shaking down
a sitting Congressman.

31:03.213 --> 31:06.181
[ Whistles ] Yeah, boy, you got
some juicy business here.

31:06.248 --> 31:08.750
If this was 1988.

31:08.817 --> 31:12.219
I'm pretty sure there'sno statute of limitations
on anything that nasty.

31:12.287 --> 31:15.055
This gets out, you'll be selling
your granddaughter's pony

31:15.123 --> 31:17.057
to pay for your legal bills.

31:27.166 --> 31:28.500
[ Chuckles ]

31:29.902 --> 31:31.835
My granddaughter's pony.

31:31.903 --> 31:34.204
I like that.

31:34.272 --> 31:37.473
But no.
You're sorely mistaken.

31:37.541 --> 31:39.407
What the hell do you mean,
"mistaken"?

31:39.475 --> 31:42.576
You don't think I knew what
a colossal pig-screw this was?

31:42.644 --> 31:45.811
I got right on top
of that mess.

31:45.879 --> 31:49.314
I caught a two-star general
with his hand in the till,

31:49.381 --> 31:51.715
happy to own it.

31:51.783 --> 31:53.752
Got him
a dishonorable discharge

31:53.820 --> 31:56.490
instead of
five years in the brig.

31:56.558 --> 31:58.092
I'm clean.

31:59.494 --> 32:01.161
He's bluffing.

32:01.229 --> 32:02.829
You have nothing,
Paul.

32:02.897 --> 32:05.130
And you're about to have
even less.

32:05.198 --> 32:06.698
You sent those boys
to their death.

32:06.766 --> 32:08.266
And now you're
messing around with --

32:08.334 --> 32:10.302
your friends
who drove me out here?

32:10.370 --> 32:12.071
They can look forward
to an audit

32:12.139 --> 32:13.839
every year
for the rest of their lives.

32:13.906 --> 32:15.106
Paul.
And you!

32:16.375 --> 32:19.845
I'll probably heap a little dirt
on <i>your</i> grave, Mr. Westen,

32:19.912 --> 32:21.379
just for the hell of it.

32:26.851 --> 32:28.819
Paul! Don't do that!
Come on! Get up!

32:28.886 --> 32:32.088
Come on.
Get off him, Paul. Come on.

32:33.757 --> 32:34.990
<i>Probably</i> shouldn't have
done that.

32:38.256 --> 32:39.789
Michael!
What happened?!

32:40.586 --> 32:41.586
He pissed me off.

32:41.612 --> 32:43.045
Mike,
what part of the plan

32:43.113 --> 32:45.548
called for assaulting
a United States Congressman?

32:45.615 --> 32:48.383
I know, but he pissed Paul off.
We got bigger problems.

32:48.451 --> 32:50.853
Vitali and his men will be here any minute.
We can't leave him here.

32:50.921 --> 32:52.588
Well, we sure as hell
can't take him with us.

32:52.656 --> 32:55.291
I am not kidnapping a member of
the House of Representatives today.

32:55.359 --> 32:57.526
Maybe after
they shoot the lot of you

32:57.594 --> 33:00.196
and drag me off to the dungeon,
he'll believe us.

33:01.898 --> 33:03.532
Two birds
with one stone.

33:03.600 --> 33:04.900
I don't think
we have a choice.

33:04.968 --> 33:06.702
Vitali's guys will come at us

33:06.769 --> 33:08.534
from all angles and all at once.

33:08.601 --> 33:11.700
We could turn this place
inside-out pretty easy,

33:11.768 --> 33:14.136
give the Congressman
a front-row seat

33:14.204 --> 33:15.837
and something to think about.

33:15.905 --> 33:18.472
It's not bad.
Well, it <i>sounds</i> bad!

33:18.540 --> 33:20.407
I think
I'll just catch a cab.

33:22.677 --> 33:23.910
(Michael) Go.

33:40.757 --> 33:41.724
Show time.

33:41.792 --> 33:43.259
I guess...

33:43.327 --> 33:45.595
I better wake him.

33:45.663 --> 33:47.363
[ Grunts, coughs ]

33:47.431 --> 33:48.698
You!
You son of a bitch!

33:48.766 --> 33:50.166
You're going to jail,
you --

33:50.233 --> 33:52.835
there's no time for that.
The Russians are coming.

33:52.903 --> 33:54.336
Right,
"the Russians are coming."

33:54.404 --> 33:55.570
They followed us here.
They're gonna kill us all.

33:55.638 --> 33:57.204
I'm calling the police.

33:57.272 --> 33:59.439
Somehow I doubt a couple
of Miami Beach patrolmen

33:59.507 --> 34:01.708
are gonna save you
from a Russian black-ops team,

34:01.776 --> 34:03.276
even if they got here on time.

34:03.344 --> 34:04.811
Give it a rest.
There are no --

34:04.878 --> 34:06.112
take a look.

34:09.482 --> 34:11.282
Oh, my God.
What the hell are they --

34:11.350 --> 34:13.618
now come on. Let's go.
Quit gawking.

34:14.985 --> 34:18.088
<i>Every country emphasizes</i>
<i>slightly different tactics</i>

34:18.156 --> 34:19.755
<i>with their elite troops.</i>

34:19.824 --> 34:21.158
<i>The Chinese Special Forces</i>

34:21.226 --> 34:22.958
<i>learn how to shoot</i>
<i>with either hand.</i>

34:23.027 --> 34:26.194
<i>The German D.S.O. teaches their</i>
<i>men to rappel from helicopters.</i>

34:26.261 --> 34:28.228
Here they come.

34:28.295 --> 34:29.429
Bring it, baby.

34:29.496 --> 34:31.429
What are you gonna do?
Build me a shed?

34:32.964 --> 34:34.998
<i>And every Russian Spetsnaz team</i>

34:35.065 --> 34:37.500
<i>is trained to siege</i>
<i>secure locations</i>

34:37.567 --> 34:41.735
<i>by surrounding, advancing,</i>
<i>and synchronizing their attack.</i>

34:41.804 --> 34:44.071
<i>Their discipline</i>
<i>makes them hard to escape</i>

34:44.139 --> 34:45.139
<i>but easy to predict.</i>

34:50.411 --> 34:52.280
[ Nail gun shoots,
Alexi grunts ]

34:53.382 --> 34:54.949
[ Muffled screaming ]

34:55.016 --> 34:57.887
(Sam) Sorry we keep
meeting like this, Alexi.

34:57.955 --> 35:00.956
<i>An all-out coordinated</i>
<i>breach has its advantages --</i>

35:01.024 --> 35:03.358
<i>maximum force,</i>
<i>the element of surprise.</i>

35:03.426 --> 35:05.160
<i>But there are drawbacks, too.</i>

35:05.227 --> 35:06.828
<i>If everyone goes in at once,</i>

35:06.896 --> 35:08.597
<i>you can find yourself</i>
<i>locked inside</i>

35:08.664 --> 35:10.931
<i>before you realize</i>
<i>your target has already left.</i>

35:19.240 --> 35:20.473
[ Vitali screams ]

35:20.541 --> 35:23.309
[ Gunshots ]

35:26.245 --> 35:27.979
[ Gunshots ]

35:34.419 --> 35:36.552
Surrender your guns
before the police arrive,

35:36.620 --> 35:37.820
and I'll show you mercy.

35:37.887 --> 35:41.190
If not...
I aim lower.

35:55.570 --> 35:57.303
[ Glass shatters ]

36:04.377 --> 36:05.543
Idiots.

36:05.611 --> 36:09.046
I only see
three guns, Vitali.

36:10.315 --> 36:13.083
[ Vitali screams,
glass shatters ]

36:13.150 --> 36:14.017
[ Thud ]

36:18.155 --> 36:20.622
Walk out backwards
with your hands up.

36:33.167 --> 36:35.668
You think this is over?

36:35.736 --> 36:37.270
For me, they will trade.

36:37.337 --> 36:39.905
They will do
prisoner exchange.

36:39.973 --> 36:42.340
For him, they will send more.

36:42.408 --> 36:44.475
We will not stop until
old man tells us everything.

36:44.543 --> 36:48.312
You will answer our questions,
and then you will die.

36:48.379 --> 36:49.946
I will volunteer for this, my --

36:50.014 --> 36:50.847
[ gunshot ]

36:52.415 --> 36:55.516
Paul!
Put the weapon down.

36:55.584 --> 36:56.984
What the hell are you doing?

36:57.052 --> 36:59.787
Are you telling me
I can't kill Russians

36:59.854 --> 37:01.655
when they invade Florida?

37:01.722 --> 37:03.389
Put your gun down, Paul.

37:06.394 --> 37:07.897
You're welcome.

37:09.267 --> 37:12.435
You...Killed him.
You killed him!

37:12.503 --> 37:13.870
In a minute,
the police will arrive.

37:13.938 --> 37:16.673
10 minutes after that,
news vans will join them.

37:16.741 --> 37:19.042
So you got to ask yourself --

37:19.109 --> 37:21.411
what story
do you want it to be?

37:21.478 --> 37:22.812
Option one --

37:22.880 --> 37:25.514
you were targeted
by rogue Russian operatives.

37:25.582 --> 37:28.684
You heroically <i>shot</i> one of them
and captured the rest.

37:28.752 --> 37:29.952
Option number two --

37:30.020 --> 37:32.122
you are secret pals
with Michael Westen,

37:32.189 --> 37:35.288
whose nefarious dealings brought
Russian terrorists to Miami.

37:35.356 --> 37:37.120
So, what's it gonna be?

37:37.188 --> 37:39.588
Michael Westen sticks around
and smiles for the camera...

37:42.792 --> 37:44.559
...Or you make some calls
for Paul?

37:50.731 --> 37:52.164
Hell...

37:52.232 --> 37:55.134
Maybe I'll even
run unopposed next time.

38:08.510 --> 38:10.378
[ Sighs ]

38:10.445 --> 38:11.779
Trash.

38:12.621 --> 38:13.956
I'm not gonna miss that job.

38:13.974 --> 38:16.175
Well, now that you got your pension
back, you gonna work in Virginia?

38:16.243 --> 38:19.244
I was thinking
about maybe writing my memoir.

38:19.312 --> 38:22.080
Don't worry. I'm not gonna
put them online or anything.

38:22.148 --> 38:23.848
You can publish them
after I'm dead.

38:23.916 --> 38:25.650
Well, that shouldn't be
anytime soon,

38:25.717 --> 38:27.384
as long as you
keep your head down.

38:27.452 --> 38:29.753
The feds are gonna
keep an eye on you.

38:29.821 --> 38:33.256
I just hope they've relocated
some lady spooks up there.

38:33.324 --> 38:35.657
Got to be <i>somebody</i> in Newport
for old...

38:35.725 --> 38:37.125
What the hell's my name?

38:39.094 --> 38:41.059
Paul Vandermark.

38:44.799 --> 38:46.134
Got to be a story there.

38:47.337 --> 38:51.274
What, did you do some job
in a German Castle or something?

38:51.342 --> 38:53.209
[ Chuckles ]

38:54.412 --> 38:56.680
I don't remember.

38:59.784 --> 39:01.752
It's not <i>just</i>
<i>when you drink, is it?</i>

39:06.891 --> 39:08.591
Well...

39:08.659 --> 39:11.093
I guess that's the last of it.

39:13.363 --> 39:16.232
All you really have
in the end...

39:16.300 --> 39:17.700
Are your stories.

39:22.704 --> 39:25.399
Can you handle
the rest of it, kid?

39:35.735 --> 39:37.769
The bank you're looking for
is Miami Trust.

39:37.837 --> 39:40.105
You got the details
for the heist all in there.

39:40.172 --> 39:41.739
Everything I could get.

39:41.807 --> 39:44.108
Thanks, Marv.

39:45.677 --> 39:46.510
Listen.

39:48.279 --> 39:50.814
I want you to tell Jesse
that I never doubted him.

39:50.881 --> 39:52.248
There was just
never enough there

39:52.316 --> 39:53.983
for me to make a case
to get him reinstated,

39:54.051 --> 39:56.719
but you tell him...
That I believed him.

39:56.787 --> 39:59.755
W-what are you talking about?

40:01.257 --> 40:02.857
Jesse's key-card entries,
computer login.

40:02.925 --> 40:04.993
There were these discrepancies
in the timing

40:05.060 --> 40:06.327
on the day he got fired.

40:06.395 --> 40:08.362
It's like somebody
had a duplicate key card.

40:08.430 --> 40:09.663
Really?

40:09.731 --> 40:12.365
Oh, the security footage --
it's all gone.

40:12.433 --> 40:13.500
It's confiscated.

40:15.002 --> 40:18.370
But you get somebody with
the clearance to track it down,

40:18.438 --> 40:21.506
you'll get a good look
at the guy who did...

40:21.574 --> 40:24.042
What they pinned on Jesse.

40:27.078 --> 40:28.846
[ Sighs ]

40:36.820 --> 40:39.055
They must have been
three serious pros

40:39.122 --> 40:41.957
to get into the vault,
wire this safety-deposit box,

40:42.025 --> 40:44.358
and get out
without showing their faces.

40:44.426 --> 40:47.027
Three serious pros
with seriously rotten luck.

40:47.095 --> 40:49.529
If it wasn't for
a random security sweep,

40:49.596 --> 40:51.898
we'd be looking at
a picture of a hole in a wall.

40:51.966 --> 40:54.201
I'm about to go, uh,
scout the bank.

40:54.268 --> 40:55.669
Anybody want to join me?

40:55.736 --> 40:57.337
Maybe tomorrow.

40:59.207 --> 41:01.475
O...Kay?

41:01.543 --> 41:02.943
Um...All right.

41:03.011 --> 41:05.245
Listen, hey,
I can't thank you guys enough.

41:05.313 --> 41:06.313
So, uh...

41:06.380 --> 41:07.781
I'll see you later.
[ chuckles ]

41:10.184 --> 41:12.084
[ Door opens, closes ]

41:12.152 --> 41:13.118
Oh, Fi --

41:13.186 --> 41:14.219
Oh!

41:14.287 --> 41:16.521
You know what I did
tonight?!

41:16.589 --> 41:18.056
I destroyed evidence

41:18.124 --> 41:20.358
that would have led Jesse to
finding out that you burned him.

41:23.862 --> 41:25.062
Thank you.

41:25.130 --> 41:26.463
"Thank you."

41:26.531 --> 41:27.597
[ Scoffs ]

41:28.666 --> 41:30.033
Fi. Fi!

41:30.100 --> 41:31.600
What we're doing is worth it.

41:31.668 --> 41:33.135
This is bigger
than one person's career.

41:33.203 --> 41:34.603
There are so many people
out there --

41:34.671 --> 41:35.838
I can't stand this!

41:37.140 --> 41:39.441
I can't stand lying to Jesse.

41:39.509 --> 41:41.643
I can't stand watching you keep
this secret like it's nothing!

41:43.679 --> 41:45.479
I can't stand
what you're turning into.

41:45.547 --> 41:46.714
Which is what?

41:50.584 --> 41:54.120
Someone who only cares
about the <i>idea</i> of people...

41:54.187 --> 41:56.354
Who doesn't give a damn

41:56.422 --> 41:58.189
about the ones who have his back
every single day.

42:00.392 --> 42:02.126
You know me
better than that.

42:04.195 --> 42:05.829
I used to think so.

